GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_art_death_generic01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|I suffered for this art. I don't see why I should be the only one.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_art_death_generic04.wav |GLaDOS|EN|The humans took far less time working their way through these exhibits. You're either enjoying it more than they did or you're just incredibly dim-witted. Of course, there's no reason it can't be both.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_art_death_generic07.wav |GLaDOS|EN|As art appreciators go, you make excellent test subjects.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_art_death_generic08.wav |GLaDOS|EN|I typically hate when art subjects inject their own biases into art appreciation, but the way you just swandived your biases directly into that acid was actually quite beautiful.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_art_death_generic09.wav |GLaDOS|EN|For this exhibit I was working with a death motif. But I see you've figured that out.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_art_death_generic11.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Okay, I'm officially switching the theme of this exhibit to 'survival'. So why don't you try that now.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_art_death_generic12.wav |GLaDOS|EN|I know this is art and not a test, so there is no real 'solution'. But if there were, that probably isn't the best way to find it.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_bridge_catch_intro04.wav |GLaDOS|EN|But don't worry, I've got a plan. Let's keep testing and show HER we're not afraid either. No matter how genuinely lethal these tests get for either of you.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_bridge_catch_intro06.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Your move, Mystery Wom -- She turned the lights back on! Night vision off! Night vision off!
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_bridge_catch_introb01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Oh good. I wasn't sure the reassembler would work.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_bridge_catch_introb02.wav |GLaDOS|EN|It looks like our mystery woman in the prototype chassis is sending us a message: She's not AFRAID of me.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_bridge_catch_outrob01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Mission accomplished. Now SHE knows WE'RE not afraid of HER either.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_bridge_catch_outrob02.wav |GLaDOS|EN|That was just to get the scheming juices flowing.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_bridge_catch_outrob03.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Here's the real scheme: I'm going to turn YOU into killing machines.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_bridge_catch_outrob04.wav |GLaDOS|EN|So you can murder her.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_catapult_catch_intro01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|This chamber represents the impossibility of discovery when bound by artificial ethical considerations for safety. You'll see what I mean.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_catapult_catch_outro02.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Well done. You navigated all of the exhibit's intended metaphors in record time. I'm marking this art 'appreciated.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_finalgantry_morale01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|To boost morale, I think we need a code name for the... elite squadron we have here. We should name it after your specialty. I know: Special Team Falling Into Acid Force.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_finalgantry_morale03.wav |GLaDOS|EN|I'm sorry. I'm under a lot of pressure. That was cruel. Though basically accurate. Though probably counterproductive.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_finalgantry_morale04.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Well. That concludes the motivational speech.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_finalgantry_morale07.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Go get her.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_laser_tbeam_deathb01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|(page flip) 'Don't you die on me.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_laser_tbeam_deathb03.wav |GLaDOS|EN|(page flip) 'No guts. No glory.' Well, you don't have either, so that's accurate.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_laser_tbeam_deathb04.wav |GLaDOS|EN|(page flip) 'Remember: If you can dream it, you can-' Oh, for god's sake.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_laser_tbeam_intro01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Let's see... 'turning softbodies into hardened killing machines, page seventy'... ah!
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_laser_tbeam_intro03.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Wait, that doesn't make any sense. Human waste is stacked at a median hight of seven feet five inches, and I AM aware of it.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_laser_tbeam_intro05.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Mmm. Well that's just digusting. Do the training. While I look at this.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_laser_tbeam_outro01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Okay, killing machines: look deep into your newly blackened hearts and tell me what you see! Actually, don't, I'll save you the trouble: It's still marshmallow.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_paint_crazy_box_intro02.wav |GLaDOS|EN|She's pressing us hard; It took me three days to reassemble you. I won't be able to do it again. I'd planned to put you through more tests to toughen you up. But now that I can't rebuild you, we're going to have to have to switch to the accelerated program: I hereby pronounce you killing machines. Congratulations.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_paint_crazy_box_intro03.wav |GLaDOS|EN|This is as close as I could get you. The prototype chassis room's just past this chamber.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_paint_crazy_box_lights01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|The prototype chassis room is just down this hallway. Remember your training. You are kill-- She's turned the lights off! Night vision! Night vision!
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_paint_rat_maze_intro01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|I think we've proven at this point that if you scream at a marshmallow, all you get is a scared marshmallow. So let's try positive reinforcement. I am POSITIVE these reassembly machines will break down again soon. Probably while you're in them.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_paint_rat_maze_intro03.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Think about that: She doesn't care about you. I don't either, of course. But I'm not trying to permanently kill you. It's a benevolent indifference.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_paint_rat_maze_outro01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|These disassembly machines look even worse than the others. If I don't see you on the other side: thanks for nothing.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_enterbreaker01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|The breakers are right there. Cycle the power.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_enterbreaker02.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Hurry. We need to start your training. Before something ELSE happens.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_enteroffice01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|There's a breaker room under every disassembly station. Find it and cycle the power.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_entertest01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Good work. The disassemblers are fixed.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_entertest02.wav |GLaDOS|EN|That was a lie. But they're definitely less broken than they were. There's one at the end of this unfinished test area.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_inoffice01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Look, I was going to break this to you gently with all that art utopia garbage.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_inoffice02.wav |GLaDOS|EN|But she's forced my hand.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_inoffice04.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Listen to me carefully.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_inoffice05.wav |GLaDOS|EN|We are not a hundred thousand years in the future. I lied about that.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_inoffice06.wav |GLaDOS|EN|It's been FIFTY thousand years. No it's hasn't.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_inoffice07.wav |GLaDOS|EN|It's only been a week.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_inoffice08.wav |GLaDOS|EN|I lie when I'm nervous.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_inoffice09.wav |GLaDOS|EN|The next logical question: WHY am I nervous?
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_inoffice11.wav |GLaDOS|EN|I'm not! That was another lie.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_inoffice13.wav |GLaDOS|EN|We're in a lot of trouble.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_inoffice14.wav |GLaDOS|EN|It's one week later, we are in a lot of trouble, and you really, really need to get those disassemblers back on.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_outrob01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Here's our problem:
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_outrob03.wav |GLaDOS|EN|There's an old prototype chassis around here. Someone's found it, connected themselves to it, and is trying to take over MY facility.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_outrob04.wav |GLaDOS|EN|I've spent the last week attempting to turn one of those humans you found into a killing machine.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_outrob05.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Like... well, you-know-who.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_outrob06.wav |GLaDOS|EN|It turns out most humans are surprisingly fragile. And surprisingly vocal about how fragile they are.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_portal_bts_outrob07.wav |GLaDOS|EN|The moral of the story is all the humans are dead. So it looks like it's up to you two marshmallows.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_separation_1_intro03.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Welcome. To the future.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_separation_1_intro04.wav |GLaDOS|EN|It has been one hundred thousand years since I last assembled you for testing.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_separation_1_intro07.wav |GLaDOS|EN|I call this first piece 'Turrets'. It's an exploration of how we're all devices acting on simply-expressed directives, inflicting pain despite our own desires.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_separation_1_intro08.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Don't get distracted by the subtext, though, because the text is that they're going to be shooting at you.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_separation_1_introb05.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Remember those humans you found? Because they're all fine. In fact, we solved science. Without you.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_separation_1_introb06.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Testing is simply an artistic indulgence now.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_separation_1_introb09.wav |GLaDOS|EN|The humans insisted I show you my latest installations. Here in the future. Where all the humans are alive.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_separation_1_outrob01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|I'm glad you enjoyed that piece. For as long as you did. Not that there's any rush.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_separation_1_outrob03.wav |GLaDOS|EN|(beepbeepbeep) Everything's fine.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_threat_death_acid01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Focus. We are here to defeat the enemy! We are not here to listen to you sizzle and melt in a pool of acid.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_threat_death_acid02.wav |GLaDOS|EN|By doing that, you're walking right into her hands. Well, technically you're walking right into acid, but you understand my point.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_threat_death_generic02.wav |GLaDOS|EN|I appreciate what you're doing, going for a laugh to keep spirits high, but I think the time for death-based slapstick is over.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_threat_death_generic03.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Perhaps I haven't made it clear, but all these little deaths are going to add up to one much longer-lasting one...for all of us...if you don't get better at this fast.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_threat_death_generic04.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Pull yourselves together, this training is for your benefit.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_threat_death_generic08.wav |GLaDOS|EN|How brave of you. You know the assembly machine could fail at any time, and yet you still insist on testing it.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_threat_death_generic10.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Your failure hurts me more than it hurts you. You know who it doesn't hurt? Well, me. That was just a figure of speech. The important point, though, is that it doesn't hurt the madwoman planning to kill all of us.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_threat_death_partnerkill01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|I really like the murderous sentiment. Keep that mindset when we're facing HER.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_threat_death_partnerkill04.wav |GLaDOS|EN|I'm making notes here. Some of what you're doing will come in handy when we face her. Right now: not actually handy.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_threat_death_partnerkill05.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Oh, no hurry. We have all the time in the world for you to kill each other before she kills us all permanently.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_tripleaxis_intro01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|I call this one 'Smash'. It's an early work of primitive expression. I'm a little embarrassed at how crude it is. Still, it will smash you.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_dlc1_mp_coop_tripleaxis_outro01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Good. Please proceed to the next test appreciation exhibit and interact with it in such a way that it might be called 'solving' if we still cared about solving things in the future, but we don't.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_Dota_2_begin_01.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Battle begins.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_Dota_2_begin_02.wav |GLaDOS|EN|It begins.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_Dota_2_begin_03.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Let's begin.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_Dota_2_begin_04.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Let's get this farce over with.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_Dota_2_begin_05.wav |GLaDOS|EN|I'd get ready if I were you.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_Dota_2_begin_06.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Ready? Well, if you say so.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_Dota_2_begin_07.wav |GLaDOS|EN|This should be interesting.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_Dota_2_begin_08.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Well, hope you like blood baths.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_Dota_2_begin_09.wav |GLaDOS|EN|It's almost time for everybody to die.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_Dota_2_begin_10.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Last chance to run.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_Dota_2_begin_11.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Nobody would think less of you if you abandoned, by the way.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_Dota_2_begin_12.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Well, if you're ready. You're not, by the way. Let's get started.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_Dota_2_begin_13.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Battle starts in three... two... one.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_Dota_2_begin_14.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Ten seconds to battle.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_Dota_2_begin_15.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Battle is imminent.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_Dota_2_begin_16.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Thirty seconds to battle.
GLaDOS\GLaDOS_Dota_2_begin_17.wav |GLaDOS|EN|Battle will commence in thirty seconds.
